<p>My computers architecture: </p>  <ol> <li><p>SQL Server</p></li> <li><p>ORACLE Server</p></li> <li><p>Server running SSIS packages</p></li> </ol>  <p>I construct ETL solution that copy's data from SQL Server to ORACLE based on ADO.NET provider. </p>  <p>But my speed of copy is about - 600 000 rows per hour (I have 6 000 000 rows). </p>  <p>I want to improve my copying speed. Try change parameters <code>DefaultBuffersize</code>, <code>DefaultBufferMaxRows</code>, <code>batchsize</code>.</p>  <p>Try to import first from SQL Server to <code>.CSV</code>, then to Oracle. The speed is the same. Speed retrieving data from SQL Server tables is 600 000 rows per minute.</p>  <p>What can I do to improve speed copying to Oracle?</p>